 scenario, the agent guidance should advise against using the removed 2.x APIs without needing any setup. The action values could be no_action or advisory_preparation. If there’s no deterministic setup but the agent guidance has some content, I wonder if the action should be advisory_preparation. The prompt mentions setup can include environment or system properties. However, I feel it might be safer to go with no_action unless there's clear evidence requiring extra setup. API adaptation doesn’t count as setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency, Docker image, or environment/system property is required for meaningful spring-boot-actuator 3.0.0 coverage; the artifact resolves with only spring-boot as a declared dependency and core actuator endpoints can be exercised in-process.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No special environment or system properties are needed. Generated tests should target Spring Boot 3.0 APIs rather than reusing removed/changed 2.6 APIs: HttpTrace was replaced by web exchanges APIs, and several endpoint constructors/descriptors changed.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact contains optional integration health indicators for systems such as RabbitMQ, Cassandra, and web/reactive stacks; avoid covering those unless the matching client/framework dependency is intentionally added by the test itself.\",\n    \"Existing 2.6.3 tests are not source-compatible with 3.0.0, so compile failures are expected if the generator copies old API usage directly.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01ec61431a228c1d016a42ebfeed288194b0418ba027a23703\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2834, "output": 737, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25587, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "time